=begin pod
=TITLE Gnome::Gtk4::EmojiChooser
=head1 Description

The B<Gnome::Gtk4::EmojiChooser> is used by text widgets such as L<Gnome::Gtk4::Entry|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/Entry> or
L<Gnome::Gtk4::TextView|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/TextView> to let users insert Emoji characters.

=for image :src<asset_files/images/emojichooser.png> :width<30%> :class<inline>

B<Gnome::Gtk4::EmojiChooser> emits the I<emoji-picked>
signal when an Emoji is selected.

=head2 CSS nodes

=begin comment
popover
├── box.emoji-searchbar
│   ╰── entry.search
╰── box.emoji-toolbar
    ├── button.image-button.emoji-section
    ├── ...
    ╰── button.image-button.emoji-section

=end comment

Every B<Gnome::Gtk4::EmojiChooser> consists of a main node called popover.
The contents of the popover are largely implementation defined
and supposed to inherit general styles.
The top searchbar used to search emoji and gets the .emoji-searchbar
style class itself.
The bottom toolbar used to switch between different emoji categories
consists of buttons with the .emoji-section style class and gets the
.emoji-toolbar style class itself.

